main event: Two unidentified flying objects were observed by a civilian in Coden, Alabama on June 20, 1965.
interesting points: The observation lasted for 1 and a half minutes,The objects were visual-radar confirmed and were moving south,There were no photographs or physical evidence submitted,The conclusion suggested that the sighting was probably that of two aircraft maneuvering in the area,The report included detailed instructions for sketching the sighting and providing observational data.
